article.headline: Lehigh 76, Lafayette 58
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 21 points to lead five players in double figures as hot-shooting Lehigh topped Lafayette 76-58 on Saturday. Kyle Neptune added 18 points while Jason Mgebroff and Joe Knight each chipped in 10 for the Mountain Hawks (12-8, 5-0 Patriot League), who shot 31-for-47 (66 percent) from the floor. Andrei Capusan led Lafayette with 16 points and Andrew Brown scored 15 -- all from behind the arc -- for the Leopards (8-10, 2-3). Lafayette took a 41-40 lead on a 3-pointer by Brown with 14:15 left, but Lehigh broke the game open with a 27-9 run over the next 10 minutes. A layup by Knight put Lehigh up 67-50 with 4:14 to go. The Mountain Hawks shot 9-for-18 from beyond the arc -- 7-for-10 in the second half. After halftime, Lehigh shot a blistering 72 percent from the floor on 18-for-25 shooting.
